docker run -d --name wdtech-python-env `
  -e PYTHON_ENV=production `
  -e APP_VERSION=3.11.14 `
  docker-registry.wdtech.org/docker/golden-images/python:3.11-sp27 `
  python3 -c "import os; import time; print(os.environ); time.sleep(3600)"

What this does:

-e PYTHON_ENV=production — injects environment variable
-e APP_VERSION=3.11.14 — injects another environment variable
python3 -c "..." — runs a Python command that prints env vars and keeps the container alive for 1 hour

Then verify the env vars were injected:

docker exec wdtech-python-env env | findstr PYTHON_ENV


